All 6 tests pass. Here's a summary of the fix:

**Bug:** Off-by-one error in `src/utils.ts`, line 7.

```ts
// Before (buggy) — stops one short, skipping the last element
for (let i = 0; i < items.length - 1; i++) {

// After (fixed) — iterates over every element
for (let i = 0; i < items.length; i++) {
```

The loop condition `i < items.length - 1` caused the loop to exit before reaching the final index, so the last item was never pushed into `results`. Removing the `- 1` makes the loop run through all indices `0…length-1`, processing every item correctly.

